dataset_clean$exclusion <- ifelse(dataset_clean$ID %in% df$ID, "retained", "excluded")

data.plot <- df %>%
  pivot_longer(
    cols = c(AcciWrong, AcciPunish),
    names_to = "Type_moral_judgment") %>%
    rename("Moral_judgment" = value)

data.plot$Type_moral_judgment_f <- factor(data.plot$Type_moral_judgment)
levels(data.plot$Type_moral_judgment_f) <- c("Punishment", "Moral wrongness")


plot.main <- ggplot(data.plot, aes(x = PSQI_TOT, y = Moral_judgment)) +

4.1 Planned

ctrl.wrong.crt6 <- with(df, cor.test(~AcciWrong + CRT6mean))
ctrl.punish.crt6 <- with(df, cor.test(~AcciPunish + CRT6mean))

ctrl.punish.crt3 <- with(df, cor.test(~AcciPunish + CRT3mean))

5 Additional analyses

5.1 Variable creation

df.mixed <- df %>%
  pivot_longer(
    cols = c(AttemptWrong, AttemptPunish,
             IntentWrong, IntentPunish,
             AcciWrong, AcciPunish,
             NeutralWrong, NeutralPunish),
    names_to = "Type_moral_judgment") %>%
    rename("Moral_judgment" = value)

df.mixed$Type_judgment <- with(
  df.mixed, 
  ifelse(grepl("Wrong", Type_moral_judgment, fixed = TRUE), "Wrong", "Punish"))

  
df.mixed$Type_scenario <- with(
  df.mixed, 
  ifelse(grepl("Attempt", Type_moral_judgment, fixed = TRUE), "Attempt", 
         ifelse(grepl("Intent", Type_moral_judgment, fixed = TRUE), "Intent",
                ifelse(grepl("Acci", Type_moral_judgment, fixed = TRUE), "Acci", 
                       ifelse(grepl("Neutral", Type_moral_judgment, fixed = TRUE), "Neutral", NA)))))

df.clean <- df.mixed %>%
  pivot_longer(
    cols = c(PSQI_TOT, PSQI_DURATION,
             PSQI_ACUTE_TOT, PSQI_ACUTE_DURATION),
    names_to = "SleepMarker") %>%
    rename("sleep" = value)

5.2 Linear mixed model

model.test.tot <- lme4::lmer(
  Moral_judgment ~ SleepMarker * sleep * Type_scenario * Type_judgment + (1 + Type_judgment | ID), 
  data = df.clean)

6.2 TOST

cor_mat <- RcmdrMisc::rcorr.adjust(as.matrix(df_cor))
cor_df <- as.data.frame(cor_mat$R[[1]])
cor_df_TOST_transit <- cor_df[which(grepl("PSQI", row.names(cor_df), fixed = TRUE)), ]
cor_df_TOST_transit$IV <- row.names(cor_df_TOST_transit)
cor_df_TOST <- cor_df_TOST_transit %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(AcciPunish, AcciWrong
                        , IntentPunish, IntentWrong,
                        AttemptPunish, AttemptWrong,
                        NeutralPunish, NeutralWrong
                        ), names_to = "DV", values_to = "value")

function_tost <- function(x, eq, asso) {
  res <- NA
  res <- TOSTER::TOSTr(
    n = nrow(df_cor), 
    r = as.numeric(as.character(x)), 
    low_eqbound_r = -eq, 
    high_eqbound_r = eq, 
    alpha = 0.05, 
    verbose = FALSE, plot = FALSE
    )
  return(
    data.frame(
      test_tost = ifelse(res$TOST_p1 < .05 & res$TOST_p2 < .05, "within the [-.25; .25] eq. bounds", "not within the [-.25; .25] eq. bounds"),
      Low_eq = res$LL_CI_TOST,
      High_eq = res$UL_CI_TOST,
      test_p1 = res$TOST_p1,
      test_p2 = res$TOST_p2,
      p_NHST = res$NHST_p)
    )
}
res_tost_small <- do.call(rbind, lapply(cor_df_TOST$value, function_tost, eq = 0.25)); 
res_tost_small <- cbind(IV = cor_df_TOST$IV, DV = cor_df_TOST$DV, res_tost_small)
res_tost_small[order(res_tost_small$p_NHST), ] %>% 
 kbl() %>%
